
ABSTRACT

The PG Accommodation Finder is a frontend-based web application designed to simplify the process of discovering and managing Paying Guest (PG) accommodations for students and working professionals. The system addresses common challenges such as information scarcity, lack of transparency, and time-consuming manual searches by providing a centralized digital platform.
The application is developed using React 18, React Router DOM, and TailwindCSS, following a component-based architecture. It supports dual user roles—accommodation seekers and PG owners—each with dedicated dashboards and role-specific functionalities. Key features include advanced search and filtering, booking request management, listing administration, and a review and rating system to enhance transparency.
The application adopts a frontend-only architecture, utilizing the browser’s localStorage for client-side data persistence. This approach ensures fast performance, simplicity, and ease of deployment while demonstrating core concepts of modern web application design. The system delivers a responsive, user-friendly solution that improves the efficiency of PG accommodation discovery and management, while providing a strong foundation for future backend integration.
















